<ns5684:section xmlns:ns5684="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.shell.scripting.iteration.while">

  <ns5685:title xmlns:ns5685="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">While loops</ns5685:title>
  <ns5686:para xmlns:ns5686="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    While loops perform an iteration <ns5687:emphasis xmlns:ns5687="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">while</ns5687:emphasis> a particular
    condition (a <ns5688:emphasis xmlns:ns5688="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">test</ns5688:emphasis>) holds true. Consider the following
    simple example:
    <ns5689:programlisting xmlns:ns5689="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" href="source/testWhile_sh.docbook"/>
    </ns5689:programlisting>
    Here we use the <ns5690:command xmlns:ns5690="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">shift</ns5690:command> command to shift the command-line
    arguments one left in each iteration until there are no more command-line arguments
    left. Executing the script via
    <ns5691:programlisting xmlns:ns5691="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
./testWhile.sh 1 2 3 4    
    </ns5691:programlisting>
    yields the following output
    <ns5692:programlisting xmlns:ns5692="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
adding 1
adding 2
adding 3
sum = 6
    </ns5692:programlisting>
  </ns5686:para>

</ns5684:section>